Description: This PRS SE Custom 24 is the quintessential SE instrument, designed to faithfully reflect the PRS model that started it all. The SE Custom 24 with Poplar Burl veneer comes finished in Natural, adding a distinctive new look while serving up classic PRS playability, reliability, and vibrant tone. This model keeps all the same foundational specifications as the SE Custom 24: poplar burl, mahogany back, Wide Thin maple neck with satin finish, 24 frets, 25” scale length, the PRS patented molded tremolo, and dual 85/15 “S” pickups with a 3-way blade switch and push/pull tone control for coil tapping. Ebony Fingerboard is smooth as silk Nickel Neck pickup cover is not permanent or soldered and can be removed easy. Comes with Gig Bag, tremolo bar and truss rod tool. Set up with Ernie Ball 10-46 Only played a few hours in home..... Frets are Factory flawless, Nut height, string action med/ low and plays, sounds great!! Love the satin neck! Open further inspection, I Included a picture of the tremolo cavity. The screws have been re installed from a previous owner that had a tremol No installed. The claw is mounted and seems to be slightly off center. Can be fixed easily by filling in holes and re drilling new. I set up this guitar a holds tune reasonably well but I suggest it be redone. That’s why it’s being listed at a low used price.
Title: Paul Reed Smith PRS SE Custom 24, Poplar Burl Top, Natural, 1 of 25, SN-S11452
